Porcupine Balls

1 lb ground beef
1/2 cup long grain rice
2 tbsp butter
1 small onion
1 can marinara sauce
salt and pepper

Add rice to a small pot and just barely cover with water
Cook on medium until water fully absorbed
Combine ground beef, butter, onion, rice, and spices
Form balls and bake at 350 for about an hour (until cooked ~165 degrees)